docs: correct point/band `scale.align` docs

Fix bar chart in the tutorial

Production rule for tooltip text in "Let's Make A Bar Chart Tutorial"
and related description contains some mistakes.

Since the tooltip text is not bound to any data, it has no `datum`.
Because of this, `datum === tooltip` always evaluates to false and it
makes `fillOpacity` 1 regardless of mouse hover. The reason why the
example seems to work is because of `translate` transform sends the text
outside of the screen, `(0, -2)`, when mouse is out.

[FIX] (vega): escape unicode escape sequence within regexp constructors

Escape the unicode escape sequence present in the string passed to the
regexp constructors as it triggers a SyntaxError that prevents the vega

Fix IE bug when null passed to insertBefore

Fix a error occurring in IE when an undefined value was passed to
insertBefore.

`insertBefore(newElement, referenceElement)`: If referenceElement is
null, newElement is inserted at the end of the list of child nodes.
In Internet Explorer, an undefined value as referenceElement will
throw an "Invalid argument" exception, while in rest of the modern
browsers, this works fine.

Fix bound.js: Test if subgroup has bounds to union

In one of my Vega graphs, I have nested `group` marks. My data is filterable via signals. If too much data gets filtered, some subgroups may lose all their backing data and they lose the `bounds` property. Vega then crashes downstream of the `bounds.union()` call that I patched in this commit, when it tries to update the bounds of the parent group.

This may also have an effect on vega/vega#559 which seems to crash for the same reason.

Merge reflow with changeset pulses queued for the same node.

This is a major change to the Graph scheduler and collector nodes.
Previously, collectors expected pulses to be either a changeset or
reflow. The Graph scheduler queued non-reflow pulses ahead of reflow
ones, and pruned multiple reflows of the same branch by comparing
timestamps. In some cases (similar to uwdata/vega#76), this could result
in mistaken skips of reflows. The new scheduler merges reflow and
changeset pulses queued for the same node, with collectors responding
similarly. To ensure this can be done safely, we verify that there is at
most one changeset pulse for every queued node. This change should also
increase the expressivity of signal+streaming data APIs, allowing for
both to occur within the same propagation cycle.

Add "autopad" option to View.update()

Adds a new option `autopad` to the `opt` argument of `View.update()`. If it is `true`-ish, Vega will re-run the `autopad` routine. This is useful if the size of the visualisation changes after the `update()` call.

Call `View` with `this` instead of `null`

This call was blowing up in the browser when used.

`View` is expecting to set properties on the `this` context,
and you can't set properties on `null`.

Cleanup 2 - removed trailing spaces, last line new lines

This patch should not change any functionality,
but it ensures that there will be fewer changes
in the future as many editors do this automatically.

This way if someone commits a change, and they use
an editor (like IDEA or Atom or Sublime) that
automatically remove trailing spaces, people
will concentrate just on the change of code,
and won't be bothered with the changes in spaces.

Require scale type in non-linear scales to remove ambiguity

Otherwise `test/spec/scatter_matrix.json` is ambiguous:

```json
{ 
          "name": "x",
          "range": "width",
          "zero": false,
          "round": true,
          "domain": {"data": "iris", "field": {"parent": "a.data"}}
        }
```

reverse can take a data reference

See test/spec/population.json : 

```json
{
          "name": "x",
          "type": "linear",
          "range": "width",
          "reverse": {"field": "reverse"},
          "nice": true,
          "domain": {"data": "pop2000", "field": "people"}
        }
```

Mark's "from" property should not require "data" or "mark"

Since a group mark's sub-marks from field implicitly uses the data from the parent group, the schema's restriction that a "from" field contain either a "data" or a "mark" property is not valid.
